KenolKobil to Invest $10 Million in Real-Estate Projects, Chairman Says

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-05-13T09:14:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/kenolkobil-to-invest-10-million-in-real-estate-projects-chairman-says.html
KenolKobil Ltd., a Kenyan fuel
retailer with operations in nine African nations, plans to
invest $10 million in real-estate projects, Chairman  Jacob
Segman  said.  The company, which has a 25 percent share of the oil market  of East Africa’s biggest economy, plans to develop shopping
malls in Kenya, Rwanda, Ethiopia and Zambia, Segman told
reporters today in the capital, Nairobi.  “We believe it is the future for  oil companies  to venture
into,” Segman said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
